# alipajand — Cursor Rules

This is Ali Pajand's personal portfolio — a Next.js 15 App Router site deployed on Vercel.
Detailed rules live in `.cursor/rules/`. This file summarises the most important constraints.

## Stack

Next.js 15 App Router · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS v4 · GSAP + Lenis · Resend · Jest

## Module responsibilities

- `app/`          → routes, layouts, metadata, API handlers
- `features/`     → page-level sections (colocated logic)
- `components/`   → shared reusable UI
- `data/`         → ALL static copy and structured content (source of truth)
- `content/`      → Markdown blog posts (gray-matter frontmatter)
- `utils/`        → pure helpers and custom React hooks

## Hard rules

1. All copy strings belong in `data/*.ts` — never hard-code text in JSX.
2. Default to React Server Components; add `"use client"` only for hooks/browser APIs/animations.
3. Named exports only — no default exports for components.
4. Tests colocated in `__tests__/` next to their subject; run `pnpm test` before finishing.
5. Use path aliases (`components/`, `data/`, `utils/`) — no relative `../../` climbs.
6. Import shared CTA styles from `utils/visual`, design tokens from Tailwind config.

## Forbidden without explicit approval

- Public route slugs or URLs
- `app/api/contact` (live Resend email route)
- `.env*` files or secrets
- Vercel config
- `aria-*` wiring, focus order, accessibility landmarks
- New npm deps with significant bundle cost

## Commands

```bash
pnpm dev | pnpm build | pnpm test | pnpm lint | pnpm typecheck | pnpm format
```
